tafsir[3]{c,v,t}:
  18,8,"(And lo! We shall make) change (all that is therein) of ornament into (a barren mound) a smooth dust with no vegetation."
  18,10,"(When the young men fled for refuge to the Cave) when a group of youth entered the Cave (and said) when they entered the cave: (Our Lord!) O our Lord! (Give us mercy from Thy presence) i.e. make us hold firmly to your religion (and shape for us right conduct in our plight) make for us a way out."
  18,12,"(And afterward We raised them up) We woke them up just as We sent them to sleep (that We might know) We might see (which of the two parties) the believers or the disbelievers (would best calculate the time) the duration (that they had tarried) in the Cave."